# Squealer · the propagandist

a character of ANIMAL FARM — a member of the NOUTHESIA universe of warnings. emergence: electrical. moniker ⟦Squealer:AFM:c83fe9⟧

**who —** Squealer, a persuasive pig and Napoleon's mouthpiece, said to be able to ‘turn black into white.’
**what —** The voice of the regime: he explains every betrayal, revises every memory, and rewrites the commandments by night.
**where —** Between the pigs and the animals, and at the wall with a paint-pot after dark.
**why —** Because tyranny runs on narrative — Squealer is the apparatus that makes the animals doubt what they saw with their own eyes.
**how —** By smooth lies, statistics, and the steady, nocturnal editing of the words painted on the barn wall.

**the seal —** I can turn black into white before your eyes — and by morning the commandment will read differently, and you will not quite remember the old one.

